    "Other applications of interventional robotics include oral surgery [192], ophthalmologic interventions [193], radiation therapy [191] and catheterisation [194].",
    "Furthermore, during the COVID-19 pandemic, autonomous and teleoperated oropharyngeal swab robots were introduced to help medical staff to perform COVID-19 swab sampling without close contact with patients [195,196].",
    "Additional information on interventional robotics is available in the many available reviews [13,34,92,184,189,191,194,197].Despite a number of achievements demonstrated by interventional robots, only a handful of them have reached a commercialisation stage, and even fewer have been adopted in practice.",
    "For a device to be commercially feasible, it must be accepted by third-party payers including the public and private health systems.",
